IdentificationDescription.text: Small sized newt, body' cross-section truncate, male' dorsal crest is low and smooth, fringes on hind feet relatively large and of black colour. Tail of males usually ends in a tinny and long filament. Extensive dark-brown or black spots on the back can be seen in both males and females.
